---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Refund Policy - PocketBurrito">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-gaming font-bold text-white mb-2">Refund Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-10">Last updated: February 19, 2026</p>

    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">1. Refund Eligibility</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          We want you to be satisfied with your PocketBurrito game server. If your service does not meet your expectations, you may request a refund within the eligibility window outlined below.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-gaming-dark rounded-lg p-6 mt-4 border border-gray-800">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3">48-Hour Money-Back Guarantee</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            New service purchases are eligible for a full refund within <strong class="text-white">48 hours</strong> of the initial payment, provided the server has not been used extensively. This applies to first-time purchases of a specific game server only.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">2. How to Request a Refund</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">To request a refund:</p>
        <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-300 mt-3 space-y-2">
          <li>Log in to your account at <a href="https://billing.pocketburrito.ca" class="text-gaming-accent hover:text-gaming-purple transition">billing.pocketburrito.ca</a></li>
          <li>Submit a <a href="https://billing.pocketburrito.ca/tickets/create" class="text-gaming-accent hover:text-gaming-purple transition">support ticket</a> with the subject "Refund Request"</li>
          <li>Include your service name and reason for the refund</li>
          <li>Our team will review your request within 24-48 hours</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mt-3">
          You may also reach us on <a href="https://discord.gg/gjjGWYY7" class="text-gaming-accent hover:text-gaming-purple transition">Discord</a> for faster assistance.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">3. Refund Processing</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li>Approved refunds are processed through the original payment method (Stripe or PayPal)</li>
          <li>Refunds typically appear within 5-10 business days depending on your bank or payment provider</li>
          <li>Upon refund, the associated game server will be terminated and all data permanently deleted</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">4. Plan Changes and Credits</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          If you downgrade your server plan mid-billing cycle, prorated credit may be applied to your account balance for future use. Upgrades are charged at the prorated difference for the remaining billing period.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">5. Non-Refundable Situations</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Refunds will not be issued in the following cases:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 mt-3 space-y-1">
          <li>Requests made after the 48-hour eligibility window</li>
          <li>Renewal payments (only the initial purchase is eligible for the 48-hour guarantee)</li>
          <li>Services terminated due to Terms of Service violations</li>
          <li>Services that have been used extensively during the refund window</li>
          <li>Partial billing periods after voluntary cancellation (service remains active until the end of the paid period)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">6. Cancellation</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          You may cancel your subscription at any time through the billing portal. After cancellation:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 mt-3 space-y-1">
          <li>Your server will remain active until the end of the current paid billing period</li>
          <li>No further charges will be made</li>
          <li>Server data will be deleted after the service expires</li>
          <li>We recommend downloading any important data before your service expires</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">7. Disputes</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          If you believe a charge was made in error or you are unsatisfied with a refund decision, please contact us through our support ticket system before initiating a chargeback with your bank or payment provider. We are committed to resolving disputes fairly and promptly. Chargebacks initiated without first contacting us may result in account suspension.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">8. Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          For refund requests or billing questions, please contact us through our
          <a href="https://billing.pocketburrito.ca/tickets/create" class="text-gaming-accent hover:text-gaming-purple transition">support ticket system</a>
          or join our <a href="https://discord.gg/gjjGWYY7" class="text-gaming-accent hover:text-gaming-purple transition">Discord community</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
